top : CPU usage, Memory usage, Running processes (live), System load
Key Fields:
%CPU → CPU usage per process
%MEM → Memory usage
PID → Process ID
load average → System load

df -h: Total disk space, Used space, Available space
E.g.
Filesystem   Size  Used Avail Use%
/dev/xvda1    20G   10G   10G  50%

free -h: Total RAM, Used memory, Free memory
E.g.
Mem:   2.0G  1.2G  800M

Command	                Checks	          Purpose
top	                    CPU + processes	  Live system monitoring
df -h	                  Disk	            Storage usage
free -h	                RAM	              Memory usage

Interview:
top monitors CPU and running processes in real time, df -h checks disk space usage, and free -h shows memory (RAM) usage in a human-readable format.
